text.tspan: is_branch_inst wires are a 1 bit signal indicating whether an instruction might affect control flow or not
enable input is just a signal indicating that a new instruction has been put into the pipeline, so it is safe
to load a new value into branch_hist_reg; will probably end up being equivalent to the pipeline registers
I may experiment with different methods for indexing into the prediction array but for this diagram we'll
assume I xor branch_hist_reg_out with PC_id
branch_hist input is the branch_hist reg value passed down the pipeline so that the value at the time of
the prediction can be adjusted according to the actual path taken by the branch. It is simply the value of
branch_hist_reg_out passed down the pipeline (probably a more efficient way to do this but this should be
read2_out + correction value based on is_branch_inst_wb and pcmux_sel_out
